{
  "stem": "17135.5",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 14.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Came to Auschwitz, and he agreed to take me-- he was then sent to another camp to Gleiwtiz II, a small camp about 1,500 inmates.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he agreed that they transferred me to his camp, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] because he knew about me, and for some, you know-- I don't know what motivated him.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was from the same town, so-- when they transferred me a week later to his camp, and I became his [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In other words, I was his bed man, and cleaning room, and what have you.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I tell it to you.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I had guilt feelings that tortured me for at least two, three years, even after liberation.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I felt almost guilty that I didn't do enough to prevent this.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That I didn't-- that I should have known that he was involved in--",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I-- first of all, if I would have known I wouldn't have-- I would have told him, we lost our father already.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We got, also-- while we were in Auschwitz, we knew there came a transport-- several transports from Riga, from the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So we knew that our mother is not alive, our two brothers are not alive.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We even assumed that my sister is not alive, although she survived.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "She went to Stuttof, to another camp.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And-- and-- and I would have told him, we were six children.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "If you and I survive, at least if it [? comes-- ?] [? come ?] [INAUDIBLE] there will be continuation of the family.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Why didn't you tell me?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I-- I-- I mean, it-- it-- I-- I was not allowed to talk to him, but I arranged it very carefully, and then always in-- in hiding so nobody should see me.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He said, Freddy, you have to understand, I want to save you.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
